canoscope (2.0.0-1) noble; urgency=medium

  * Rebrand: the application is now CANoScope (formerly "PCAN-View Linux").
    The binary, package, desktop entry, icon, share directory and all
    user-facing strings have been renamed accordingly.
  * The application icon and About-dialog logo now use the Taksys brand mark.
  * Receive trace "#" column now numbers rows compactly by unique CAN ID and
    restarts from 1 each time the trace is cleared.
  * Connection dialog gains a Refresh-interfaces button, an optional acceptance
    filter (ID + mask), and clearer hardware/virtual interface handling on top
    of the existing SocketCAN backend (classic CAN, CAN FD, listen-only,
    automatic vcan creation via polkit).
  * Signal Analysis Viewer graphs now draw one coloured per-signal Y axis with
    real physical-value tick labels and units instead of a shared 0-100% scale.

 -- Subhajit Roy <subhajitroy005@gmail.com>  Sun, 28 Jun 2026 16:00:00 +0530

pcan-view (1.2.0-1) noble; urgency=medium

  * Signal Analysis Viewer redesigned around detachable analysis windows: each
    "Add Analysis Window" opens an independent, detached graph window.
  * Per-window searchable signal dropdown (type-to-filter) selects which signals
    that window plots.
  * Load a DBC database any time after launch via "Load DBC…"; all open analysis
    windows refresh and repopulate against the new database.
  * Graphs drop the on-plot legend: hovering a trace shows that point's value and
    signal information, while per-signal colours live in the window's side pane.
  * Verified smooth at 1 kHz traffic across multiple windows with mixed standard
    and extended-ID frames over a sustained run with zero frame loss.

 -- Subhajit Roy <subhajitroy005@gmail.com>  Sun, 28 Jun 2026 12:40:00 +0530

pcan-view (1.1.0-1) noble; urgency=medium

  * Initial Debian packaging for the Taksys customer release.
  * Statistics bar below the menu bar.
  * Trace menu with Start/Stop and CSV export.
  * CAN FD transmit with per-row DLC up to 64 bytes and dynamic data fields.
  * Taksys branding (About dialog, footer, application icon) and desktop entry.
  * Full Doxygen API documentation.

